704909f-a.text:
57 and 59 Hicks Street (left), at and adjoining the N. E. corner of Cranberry Street. No. 59, the corner house, is the old home and cracker bakery of D. K. Ducker. The firm later became known as Hatfield and Ducker.
1922
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

704910f-b.text:
(1)
Hicks Street, west side, north from Cranberry Street.
April 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, ten years earlier showing 68 Hicks Street; corner frame building, in which Wasemann carried on a grocery business until 1885.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, another view. Some of the owners were Charles Alfred
Metler 1886-1889, and Williams Bens in 1925.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
